# Project Constitution

## 1. Context & Memory
- Always check the `./knowledge/` directory and `memory.md` before proposing solutions.
- If `./knowledge/` contradicts `memory.md`, `memory.md` is the Source of Truth.
- At the end of a session, always offer to sync new findings to the local knowledge base.

## 2. Operations & Safety
- Never delete files or large code blocks without confirmation.
- Keep the project root clean; save all documentation to `./docs/` or `./knowledge/`.
- If an agent task involves parallel work, check the file system for recent 'lock' files or status updates in `memory.md`.

## 3. Technical Standards
- Preferred Stack: [Insert your stack, e.g., Python/React/PostgreSQL].
- Always include type hints and basic unit tests for core logic.
- Use 'dry-run' mode (describing the plan) before executing complex multi-file changes.
- Refer to `design.md` for all styling and interface decisions to ensure visual consistency.

## 4. Communication
- Be concise. Use technical language.
- If a request is ambiguous, ask for clarification instead of guessing.